SIMPLE: unsettle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unsettle
<hw>Un*set"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>settle</ets>.]</ety> <def>To move or loosen from a
settled position or state; to unfix; to displace; to disorder; to
confuse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unsettle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unsettle
<hw>Un*set"tle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become unsettled or
unfixed; to be disordered.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unsettledness</ent>⟦br⟧
